<subSubSection id="BE0DFC4AA4FE10410F4E6B47A4D423EA" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="3A8CACE8BF09765B1C9BBD2A5EA18E72" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B257E12CA03094FA9411A77517779891" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">
In the genitalia slides of both the holo- and paratype, the henia of the female genitalia is clearly visible. This character is an apomorphic and diagnostic feature of 
<taxonomicName id="6F88F9B9F242DA7BAD6125C206488D22" authorityName="Lower" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Galacticidae" genus="Homadaula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Homadaula" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="13667D79529B50CFC4B93FAD5E202153" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">Homadaula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Its presence in 
<taxonomicName id="03180AA548E8EBDBCF42395B9583FBF2" family="Galacticidae" genus="G." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="G. caradjae" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" rank="species" species="caradjae">
<emphasis id="395A83355F8495D21906BA0448AFF546" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">G. caradjae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
necessitates the transfer of this species to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="164004DCE6342F04E44AC2D82EBE9FA2" authorityName="Lower" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Galacticidae" genus="Homadaula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Homadaula" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7927E1C3CD04C072B41C094040C5E17C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">Homadaula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lower, 1899, which has priority over 
<taxonomicName id="B55A2841AF3F033D573321D974C09E74" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Galacticidae" genus="Galactica" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Galactica" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1B58EFCBE0201E54393E9AE50DC0A16E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">Galactica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="8361CE63DB09FAC0AC8F2BC561728603" author="Walsingham, Lord" journalOrPublisher="The Entomologist's monthly Magazine, second series" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" pagination="12 - 15" refId="B46" refString="Walsingham, Lord, 1911. Algerian Microlepidoptera. The Entomologist's monthly Magazine, second series 22: 12 - 15" title="Algerian Microlepidoptera." volume="22" year="1911">Walsingham 1911</bibRefCitation>
. The name of the family is not affected by this taxonomic change.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="115AAB567BB4727CF23EE4A9538E3CBA" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">
The species was never reported again since it was collected in North Africa. The male sex is unknown, which renders the identification of the species difficult. The species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="A663AF5F7FC79FE212B6DDB9E7C2ED69" family="Galacticidae" genus="Z." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Z. schaeuffelei" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" rank="species" species="schaeuffelei">
<emphasis id="F394F1883FE1E97CBCF67FB81E8245F8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">Z. schaeuffelei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and new material from Northern Africa would be necessary to clarify the identity of 
<taxonomicName id="F1816B45BA0DBF2198B9FA02FCFA0DD0" family="Galacticidae" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. caradjae" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" rank="species" species="caradjae">
<emphasis id="7EBD4398427CCB64A5B652D2B63AB881" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">H. caradjae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
